* VOICE
** ACTIVE
   - active voice is unmarked
   --- tiktalen kegin :: i touch the stone
** PASSIVE
   - passive voice is marked by the addition of /tat/ after the finite verb marker /al/
   --- tiktaltatos keg memast :: the stones is touched by me

* PARTICIPLES
  - do i even still have participles?

    *_BREAKING CHANGE_*
    TENSE   ASPECT VOICE
    | simple active     | tiktalen      | I touch             |
    | imperfect active  | tiktazalen    | I am touching       |
    | perfect active    | tiktaxalen    | I have touched      |
    | simple passive    | tiktaltaten   | I am touched        |
    | imperfect passive | tiktazaltaten | I am being touched  |
    | perfect passive   | tiktaxaltaten | I have been touched |

* FRAMES
  finite infinitive participle
  finite /al/
  infinitive /ar/
  participle /azum, axum/ ????

  tiktazum :: a touching thing ==> touching
  tiktaxum :: a touched thing ==> touched


* LEXICON
  - {:jag-lexicon:}

* yadda yadda blah
** nonpast TENSE
*** kafal mem borgodh :: i go to town
*** kafal mem borgodh nodizd :: i go to town tomorrow
*** tiktal mem kegot nodizd :: i will touch the rock tomorrow
*** tiktal keg memot :: the rock touches me

** past TENSE
*** kafal-tat mem borgodh wodizd:: i went to town yesterday
*** tiktal-tat borg memot wodizd:: i touched the rock

** active participles
*** kafaz :: active participle :: going
*** i mem kafaz borgodh :: BE i going to-town
*** kafazal mem borgodh :: go-actPrtcpl-finiteV i town-DAT

